mdbook.md
     1в†’# mdBook-specific features
     2в†’
     3в†’## Hiding code lines
     4в†’
     5в†’There is a feature in mdBook that lets you hide code lines by prepending them with a specific prefix.
     6в†’
     7в†’For the Rust language, you can prefix lines with `# ` (`#` followed by a space) to hide them [like you would with Rustdoc][rustdoc-hide].
     8в†’This prefix can be escaped with `##` to prevent the hiding of a line that should begin with the literal string `# ` (see [Rustdoc's docs][rustdoc-hide] for more details)
     9в†’
    10в†’[rustdoc-hide]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/rustdoc/write-documentation/documentation-tests.html#hiding-portions-of-the-example
    11в†’
    12в†’```bash
    13в†’# fn main() {
    14в†’    let x = 5;
    15в†’    let y = 6;
    16в†’
    17в†’    println!("{}", x + y);
    18в†’# }
    19в†’```
    20в†’
    21в†’Will render as
    22в†’
    23в†’```rust
    24в†’# fn main() {
    25в†’    let x = 5;
    26в†’    let y = 6;
    27в†’
    28в†’    println!("{}", x + y);
    29в†’# }
    30в†’```
    31в†’
    32в†’When you tap or hover the mouse over the code block, there will be an eyeball icon (<i class="fa fa-eye"></i>) which will toggle the visibility of the hidden lines.
    33в†’
    34в†’By default, this only works for code examples that are annotated with `rust`.
    35в†’However, you can define custom prefixes for other languages by adding a new line-hiding prefix in your `book.toml` with the language name and prefix character(s):
    36в†’
    37в†’```toml
    38в†’[output.html.code.hidelines]
    39в†’python = "~"
    40в†’```
    41в†’
    42в†’The prefix will hide any lines that begin with the given prefix. With the python prefix shown above, this:
    43в†’
    44в†’```bash
    45в†’~hidden()
    46в†’nothidden():
    47в†’~    hidden()
    48в†’    ~hidden()
    49в†’    nothidden()
    50в†’```
    51в†’
    52в†’will render as
    53в†’
    54в†’```python
    55в†’~hidden()
    56в†’nothidden():
    57в†’~    hidden()
    58в†’    ~hidden()
    59в†’    nothidden()
    60в†’```
    61в†’
    62в†’This behavior can be overridden locally with a different prefix. This has the same effect as above:
    63в†’
    64в†’~~~markdown
    65в†’```python,hidelines=!!!
    66в†’!!!hidden()
    67в†’nothidden():
    68в†’!!!    hidden()
    69в†’    !!!hidden()
    70в†’    nothidden()
    71в†’```
    72в†’~~~
